---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { t } from '../../i18n';

const locale = 'en';
---

<BaseLayout title={t(locale, 'company.title')} locale={locale}>
  <section class="section page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="accent-line" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      <h1>{t(locale, 'company.heading')}</h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section container">
    <div class="content-width reveal">
      <p>
        La Tulpa is a contemporary dance company directed by Manuel Monró. It was founded in 2023, following his participation in the XVI Festival Internacional Escena Mobile de Arte y Diversidad, held at the Teatro Alameda in Seville from 21 to 24 September 2023.
      </p>

      <p>
        Escena Mobile is an inclusive arts and diversity festival held annually in Seville since 2007. La Tulpa was born in that context: at the crossroads of contemporary creation and inclusive dance.
      </p>

      <h2 class="reveal">The language</h2>
      <span class="accent-line" aria-hidden="true"></span>

      <p class="reveal">
        Contemporary dance and dance theatre in the field of inclusive creation. Simple, precise movement. Scenic research. Chiaroscuro aesthetics. Each piece seeks the threshold between the visible and the contained.
      </p>

      <h2 class="reveal">The name</h2>
      <span class="accent-line" aria-hidden="true"></span>

      <p class="reveal">
        A tulpa is, in its Tibetan origin, a being that takes form through thought and will. A thought made flesh. The image resonates with the company's poetics: bodies that embody what cannot be said in words.
      </p>

      <aside class="placeholder-content reveal">
        Confirm with Manuel the personal meaning he attributes to the company name.
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    padding-top: calc(4rem + var(--space-xl));
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .content-width p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .content-width h2 {
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .content-width aside {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }
</style>
